Paul Doyle moved his family into £820,000 home in Altrincham, Cheshire . 
  Father-of-two was jailed for 16 years after being unmasked as head of drugs ring . 
  He put down £200,000 deposit and obtained £600,000 mortgage by falsely claiming his wife Jeanette worked as a company executive . 
  Doyle admitted supplying class A and B drugs between 2012 and 2014 . 
  He was claiming tax credits and incapacity handouts despite never working . 
  Police raided his five-bedroom home in July 2014 and found £15million of cocaine and heroin . 
 